<h1>Conclusion</h1>

<!-- CONTENIDO -->
<section>

    <p>
        The Cattedrale di Santa Maria del Fiore represents one of the most remarkable achievements in architectural and cultural history. Its construction reflects the artistic ambition and technological innovation of the Renaissance period, particularly through the groundbreaking work of Filippo Brunelleschi and the creation of its iconic dome.

        This project allowed us to explore the cathedral not only from a historical and architectural perspective but also through a structured digital approach using RDF and SPARQL queries. By organizing information into connected data, it becomes possible to better understand the relationships between historical figures, architectural elements, and cultural context.

        Overall, this work demonstrates how digital tools can enhance the study and preservation of cultural heritage, making complex historical information more accessible, organized, and meaningful for academic and educational purposes.
    </p>

